# Security, Privacy, and Compliance Rules

- Secrets & Identity
  - Use Managed Identity; secrets in Key Vault only.
  - Never commit `.env`; use `.env.example` templates.
- Data Protection
  - Encrypt at rest/in transit; CMK where required.
  - Respect data residency; pin regions appropriately.
  - Minimize PII; redact logs; segregate tenant data.
- Network
  - Private endpoints for model, storage, search. No public egress unless approved.
- Access
  - RBAC least privilege; audit all admin actions and approvals.
- AI Safety
  - Enable content filters; block prompt injection vectors; constrain tools.
- Compliance
  - Keep DPIA/DTIA where applicable; retention policies enforced.